				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I just could not wait! I had to give it a shot- so I tackled the first part of the beastlord epic!
<br />

<br />
Basically, those not familiar with BL epics, the epic consists of handing a polished acrylia spear (bought off nearby vendor in outpost in grimling forest) to scout Husman, who then wants you to help fight grimling in the grimling fort across the bridge-
<br />

<br />
The mobs are not hard, but the problem is nor is scout Husman, who is the same level as the grimlings (about 30ish something)
<br />

<br />
Your goal is to keep him alive during the first attack to clear the fort and the proceding 5 waves of grimlings that follow. On the 6th wave the grimling officer spawns and you kill him, take his scalp and turn it into Scout Husman (who should still be alive)and he gives you the 'medal of war' that completes the quest.
<br />

<br />
I had a few problems however making me think I could not do this:
<br />

<br />
a.) the scout cannot be healed or buffed- nor does he regenerate hitpoints between waves- so he can only take so many hits til he dies, making the quest a failure. All guides and posts regarding this on the web all say one full group is needed in the 50 range or at least 3 55 levels to keep him alive. Well, my one guildie partner is in bootcamp and the other can't get on at all due to connections problems. Also our friendly 53 cleric lost her DSL company and can't get on, leaving me by myself on this as all other guildies are too low in level to help.
<br />

<br />
b.) I have my own connection problems, and if I go LD it could be hours til my cable comes back on. The 'scalp' off the grimling is 'no rent' so if I suffer a LD I'm screwed.
<br />

<br />
c.) I also suffer random crashes, could be once an hour, 3 times an hour or once every 2hrs depending on my luck- if I crash the scout is dead- he cant kill one grimling on his own let alone a whole camp and 5 preceding waves.
<br />

<br />
Given the above situation I thought it only logical to give this quest a try!
<br />

<br />
So I run to Grimling Forest, crashing on zone in- (good sign,lol) Find the vendor with the ore and buy it (54p) and give Scout Husman the ore to activate the quest- he says something about our mission to kill grimlings, mentions I must keep him alive or the quest is a failure and whipes out his sword and shield- ........then just sorta stands there for awhile.... then finally starts walking out of the camp instucting me to stay behind him and keep low- good Idea as I'm not real sure which nearby grimling camp he's heading to-
<br />

<br />
We get on a hill overlooking the grimling camp (man this guy walks slow) and he says wait til he gives the word - which comes about 3 minutes later and he dashes into the camp-
<br />

<br />
Now my first plan on doing this solo was to set up an assist key for scout Husman and simply have my pet attack what he attacks- only problem I found with this is that he doesn't always attack whats attacking him- and while you fighting one 3 others are beating on him. So the assist key idea was a flop.
<br />

<br />
After i realize the assist key idea was a no go i quickly hit every grimling around the scout to gain argo, which my pet will automatically attacks once they hit back. This approach works to some degree except for the casters not near the scout, here you must constantly rotate looking for them and have pet attack- 
<br />

<br />
In the end the scout lived til the middle of the 3rd wave- not to bad but still a failure.
<br />

<br />
Well, I was close, i just need to refine my approach so i tried again- another 54p and a new idea.......sit. Mobs always attack sitters first, and I figured if i simply sit beside the scout I would automatically have the argo-
<br />

<br />
Well, worked to some degree, but not all green conning mobs attack, even when sitting. so a combination of sitiing, hitting and targeting everything I could click my mouse on eventually had my targeting and attacking the scout by accident- he survived my pet for about 6 seconds- blah!
<br />

<br />
3rd times a charm! another 55p and a quest restart (he respawns in about 20 minutes) using the sit and target everything approach got me to wave 4. Then the scout dies- 
<br />

<br />
So.....what would happen if I simply stayed in the camp?
<br />

<br />
2 waves later the chief shows up- I kill him and get the no rent scalp.
<br />

<br />
Okay- now is not the time to go LD- 
<br />

<br />
Wait til scout respawns and hand him the scalp, get the "I do not need that item" and the item back response- ok- 
<br />

<br />
Maybe restart quest- so another 55p and in the camp we go...
<br />

<br />
After the 1st wave he still won't take the scalp- but during the third wave in all the battle spam I read him saying something about giving him the scalp from the officer so tried again- he won't take it, in fact trade window wouldn't even come up- but he was being attacked during this and soon died-
<br />

<br />
Okay, I need to wait for him to mention the scalp then wait for a period between attack waves to hand this in to him-
<br />

<br />
Another 55p and after the third wave he accepted the scalp and gave me the Medal of War!
<br />

<br />
So, you can do this Solo! 
<br />

<br />
My guess is the scout will only accept the scalp once the grimling officer is up- though he is in the sixth wave I believe he actually spawns elsewhere during the third wave and it merely takes him 2 waves to get to the camp- as i noticed all waves of grimlings coming from over the hills in 3 different directions.
<br />

<br />
So the secret......
<br />

<br />
Only need to keep scout alive to the third wave, at which time the other waves and the officer have already spawned and are on their way- simply wait and kill officer and get the scalp-
<br />

<br />
repeat the quest with your scalp in hand from previous try, after wave 3 turn it in to scout for your medal of war and go back and turn that in at Vahl Shir BL guild to finish!
<br />

<br />
Now- how to finish the rest solo without help from guild? Sit in PoK and beg in OOC for help or even pay- say 500p per member for help- that would be 2500p per group. in the end 15k per six camps- then simply get the padding,gems ect on my own and ooc in fungus for the end-
<br />

<br />
who needs a guild's help anyway- those epics are worth 15k easy!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
